    "To migrate, an engineer writes each update to both the old and new database in application code ('dual write'). Occasionally the two stores disagree. Why does naive dual-write drift, and what is a more reliable approach?",
    "Without a transaction or a single source of truth, one write can succeed while the other fails (or they interleave), so the stores diverge; use change-data-capture or write to one store and replicate, rather than two independent writes.",
